About "The Fog Lifter"
        
        
            Gary Blackford is a man with a story to tell. After sinking into the blackness of depression and mental illness to the point of attempting suicide, Gary tells a story of great hope to a generation struggling with the mind. He begins by taking the reader into the dark caverns of the mind. 


This story may shock some, yet gives an incredible insight into what someone suffering in this way can go through. Then like refreshing gusts of wind, the nine steps toward recovery start to blow the fog away. Each step making the road ahead a little clearer, till the fog lifts, the sun shines through, and the beauty of life is visible again. 


Honest, humorous and easy to read, this book is all about making life a better place to live.
- Publisher. 
- Koorong

From a world darkened by depression and mental illness comes a message of hope to this generation

 Gary Blackford is a man with a story to tell. After sinking into the blackness of depression and mental illness to the point of attempting suicide, Gary now tells a story of great hope to a generation struggling with the mind. He begins by taking the reader into the dark caverns of the mind showing his personal struggle. This story may shock some, yet give an incredible insight into what someone suffering from depression and mental illness can go through. Then like taking steps from a dark cellar into the open light, Gary leads us step by step through 9 practical steps into the light.
 This book has been over 20 years in the making and told in a very real and at times quite humorous way.
- Publisher


        Meet the Author
    

Gary Blackford
I have been on an incredible journey. My journey, like all journeys has had some high mountain top experiences and some deep, cold and extremely dark valleys as well. I used to think I was alone in my suffering, but now I know that so many live where I once lived. My passion is to help lead as many as possible to a life beyond the confines of depression and mental illness. Around the age of 16-17, life for me shifted and I began walking a road that would lead me to darker places than I ever imagined existed in my mind. Hallucinations, paranoia, paralysing fear and depression became constant companions, an all consuming blackness that culminated in a suicide attempt in 1986. Yet, now I'm a Senior Pastor, biblical teacher, professional sales and business development trainer and life coach. I love life. I live and pastor in Coffs Harbour NSW Australia. I enjoy being married to my wife Robyn and have for 20+ years. I also father 4 amazing daughters. How did all this happen? The answer lies in the biblical principles I have learnt and now share. These biblical ideas, teaching and thoughts can, and have, transformed many lives. (Gary)


 Gary Blackford is the Senior Pastor of BlueCross Church Coffs Harbour, Australia. Gary and his wife Robyn live to lead people to freedom through God's Word.












