Gary D. Blackford: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg








































  





















































































July 21, 2017 6:06 PM ET

Company Overview of UHS Surgical Services, Inc.



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Gary D. Blackford  Chairman of Universal Hospital Services Inc and CEO of Universal Hospital Services Inc, UHS Surgical Services, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 6 Board Members in 6 different organizations across 7 different industries.See Board Relationships60--
Background

		Mr. Gary D. Blackford served as the Chief Executive Officer of Universal Hospital Services Inc. from 2002 to February 2, 2015 and served as its President since 2002. Mr. Blackford was employed at Critical Care Systems International, Inc. From 2001 to 2002, he served as the Chief Executive Officer at Curative Health Services. From 1999 to 2001, he served as the Chief Executive Officer of ShopforSchool, Inc. He served as the Chief Operating Officer of Value Rx from 1995 ... to 1998 and Chief Operating Officer and Chief Financial Officer of MedIntell Systems Corporation from 1993 to 1994. Mr. Blackford is a seasoned Health Care Executive, having held leadership positions at ValuRx, Curative Health and Medintell Systems. He served as the Chairman of the Board at Universal Hospital Services Inc. from 2007 to February 2, 2015 and its Director from 2002 to February 2, 2015. He has been Director of EnteroMedics Inc. since August 15, 2016 and PipelineRx, Inc. since May 10, 2016. He has been Lead Director of EnteroMedics Inc. since December 2016.  Mr. Blackford has to EnteroMedics over 30 years of executive experience in the healthcare industry. From 1994 to 1998, Mr. Blackford served in executive roles at pharmacy benefit management companies including Medintell Systems Corporation and ValueRx (acquired by Express Scripts). He has been a Non-Executive Director of Wright Medical Group N.V. since October 2015. He has been an Independent Director of Halyard Health, Inc. since October 31, 2014. He serves as Director of Genezen Healthcare, Inc. He has been a Director of Wright Medical Technology, Inc. since 2008. He served as a Non-Executive Director at Tornier N.V. since October 1, 2015. He served as a Director of Wright Medical Group Inc. since May 2008 until 2015. He served as a Director of Compex Technologies Inc. since January 24, 2005. He serves as a Member of the Board of the Twin Cities Ronald McDonald Charities, a nonprofit corporation. He holds Certified Public Accountant Certificate. Mr. Blackford holds a Bachelors of Business Administration from The University of Iowa and a Juries Doctor from Creighton University.Read Full Background




